# 🚀 Postaway — Social Media REST API

[![Node.js Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/node.js-%3E%3D20.0.0-brightgreen.svg?style=flat-square&logo=node.js)](https://nodejs.org/)
[![Express.js Framework](https://img.shields.io/badge/framework-express-blue.svg?style=flat-square&logo=express)](https://expressjs.com/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg?style=flat-square)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![API Documentation](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-swagger-green.svg?style=flat-square&logo=swagger)](http://localhost:3000/api-docs)

Postaway is a high-performance, secure backend API for a social media networking application. It provides everything necessary to build a complete social experience—including secure JWT authentication, structured post sharing (complete with image uploads), active comment threads, and post-liking systems.

---

## ⚡ Core Features

- **🔐 Secure Authentication:** Seamless User Signup and Signin yielding stateless JWT token authentication.
- **📝 Post Sharing:** Complete CRUD functionality for social posts. Supports multi-part image uploads utilizing `multer`.
- **💬 Comment Threads:** Add, edit, delete, and view comment sections attached to specific posts.
- **❤️ Like System:** Interactive post liking where users can toggle likes and retrieve detailed lists of liking users.
- **🛡️ Secure Middleware:** Restricts endpoints to logged-in users and automatically censors sensitive fields (like passwords) from system logs.
- **📋 Automated Logging:** Implements an automated audit logging system powered by `winston`.
- **📖 OpenAPI / Swagger Docs:** Beautiful, interactive API documentation served directly at `/api-docs`.

---

## 📁 Repository Structure

```text
Postaway/
├── src/
│   ├── error-handler/
│   │   └── applicationError.js     # Standardized custom error class
│   ├── features/
│   │   ├── comment/                # Router, Controller, Model for comments
│   │   ├── like/                   # Router, Controller, Model for likes
│   │   ├── post/                   # Router, Controller, Model for posts
│   │   └── user/                   # Router, Controller, Model for users
│   └── middlewares/
│       ├── fileupload.middleware.js # Multer configuration for image files
│       ├── jwt.middleware.js        # Token authentication validation
│       └── logger.middleware.js     # Winston audit logger configuration
├── upload/                          # Uploaded image files storage
├── server.js                        # App initialization and routing setup
├── swagger.json                     # OpenAPI specification definitions
└── package.json                     # Project configurations & dependencies
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Quickstart

Follow these steps to get the server running locally:

### 1. Prerequisites
Make sure you have Node.js (version 20 or higher) installed on your system.

### 2. Install Dependencies
Clone the repository and run the package installer:
```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Run the Development Server
Launch the application:
```bash
npm start
```
The server will boot and listen at `http://localhost:3000`.

### 4. Open API Documentation
Visit the interactive Swagger UI to test the endpoints:
👉 **[http://localhost:3000/api-docs](http://localhost:3000/api-docs)**

---

## 🗺️ API Endpoint Map

### 👤 User Authentication (`/api/users`)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :---: |
| `POST` | `/signup` | Registers a new user account | ❌ |
| `POST` | `/signin` | Authenticates credentials and returns a JWT token | ❌ |

### 📬 Post Management (`/api/posts`)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :---: |
| `GET` | `/all` | Fetches all posts (paginated via `page` and `pageSize` query parameters) | ✔️ |
| `GET` | `/:id` | Fetches a single post by ID | ✔️ |
| `GET` | `/` | Fetches all posts created by the logged-in user | ✔️ |
| `POST` | `/` | Creates a new post (expects multipart form data: `caption` and `image`) | ✔️ |
| `PUT` | `/:id` | Updates a post's caption or image (owner only) | ✔️ |
| `DELETE` | `/:id` | Deletes a post (owner only) | ✔️ |

### ❤️ Likes (`/like`)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :---: |
| `GET` | `/:postId` | Fetches all active likes for a specific post | ❌ |
| `GET` | `/toggle/:postId` | Toggles the like status of a post for the authenticated user | ✔️ |

### 💬 Comments (`/comment`)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :---: |
| `GET` | `/:postId` | Fetches all comments for a specific post | ❌ |
| `POST` | `/:postId` | Adds a new comment to a post | ✔️ |
| `PUT` | `/:commentId` | Updates an existing comment's content (owner only) | ✔️ |
| `DELETE` | `/:commentId` | Deletes a comment from a post (owner only) | ✔️ |

